SIMPLE: ethereous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethereous
<hw>E*the"re*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L.<ets>aethereus</ets>, Gr. <?/ See <er>Ether</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed of ether; ethereal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>ethereous</qex> mold whereon we stand.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or resembling,
ether.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ethereous oil</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Ethereal
oil</cref>, under <er>Ethereal</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etherification</ent>⟦br⟧
